cs.CR, cs.MM, cs.DB, cs.CV, cs.DS

The paper deals with privacy-preserving storage and retrieval of visual data in the cloud, which involves cryptographic schemes and content-based image retrieval. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), cs.MM (Multimedia), cs.DB (Databases), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Among these, cs.CR is the most likely category since the paper focuses on privacy and security, and proposes a novel cryptographic scheme. cs.MM and cs.CV are also likely categories since the paper deals with visual data and content-based image retrieval. cs.DB and cs.DS are less likely categories, but still possible since the paper involves storage and retrieval of large image repositories.
